# Public Cloud LRP Financial Model
**Goal:** This project builds a long‑range (5 year) financial model for public cloud consumption,cost forecasting, 
and scenario analysis. Includes baseline assessment, scenario modeling, and strategic recommendations.

**Tech Stack**
### Core Modeling
- Python (Pandas, NumPy, Scipy)
- Jupyter Notebook
- Cloud economics modeling (AWS/GCP/Azure)
### Financial Modeling
- Driver-Based Modeling (Volume & Rate Drivers)
- Monte Carlo Simulation (P10 / P50 / P90 Forecasting)
- Scenario Analysis (Base / Upside / Downside)
### Visualization
- Plotly (Interactive Fan Charts, Waterfall Charts, Scenario Comparisons)
- Matplotlib (Baseline plotting)
### Data & Validation
- Excel (LRP Model Validation)
- JSON (Model Versioning & Snapshot Storage)
### Data Engineering 
- Python-based ETL concepts (data structuring, transformation)

**Highlights**
- Built a production-style financial model in Jupyter Notebook simulating a 5-year cloud revenue forecast
- Implemented Monte Carlo simulation (10,000 runs) to generate P10 / P50 / P90 financial scenarios  
- Designed a driver-based modeling framework separating customer growth (volume) and pricing/cost drivers (rate)  
- Developed interactive Plotly dashboards including fan charts, scenario comparisons, and waterfall variance analysis  
- Translated financial logic into scalable Python models, reducing reliance on static Excel-based approaches  
- Performed Excel-to-Python validation with tolerance checks to ensure numerical accuracy  
- Built a model versioning system to track assumptions, outputs, and enable point-in-time reconstruction  
- Generated automated business commentary explaining financial changes 



